Allocate zero-based memory if prereserved memory found on x86-64

We only check for zero-based memory if a flag is turned on to use the zero-based sandbox model.
Thus, this CL also provides a scons command-line option.

BUG=http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2927
TEST=./scons nacl_helper_bootstrap x86_64_zero_based_sandbox=1 platform=x86-64
R=mseaborn@chromium.org,bradnelson@google.com

